---
description: Code style
alwaysApply: true
---
- TypeScript strict. No `any` — use `unknown` + narrowing or fix the type.
- No classes over 300 lines; split into components/helpers.
- Filenames: PascalCase.ts for classes, camelCase.ts for utilities, kebab-case for json.
- Prefer small pure functions; side effects live in systems.
- Every exported function/class gets a one-line JSDoc saying what it's for.
- Do not add dependencies without a docs/decisions/ entry.
